text.section:
Petitions pursuant to this section shall set forth:
The name and address of the ward;
The name and address of the limited guardian, guardian, limited conservator, or conservator;
The name, address, and interest of the petitioner;
The names and addresses of the ward's next of kin, if known;
The name and address of the individual or facility, if any, having custody of the ward;
The relief requested; and
The facts and reasons supporting the request.

Upon conclusion of a modification hearing without a jury, the court shall enter a written order setting forth the factual basis for its finding and may do any of the following:
Dismiss the petition;
Remove the guardian or conservator and dissolve the guardianship or conservatorship order;
Remove the limited guardian, guardian, limited conservator, or conservator and appoint a successor;
Modify the original guardianship or conservatorship order; or
Make any other order which the court deems appropriate and in the best interest of the ward.
